casebody.data:
MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

97-359. State ex rel. SuperAmerica Group, Div. of Ashland, Inc. v. Adzic.

In Mandamus and Prohibition. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for writs of mandamus and prohibition and was considered in a manner prescribed by law. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that relator’s claim in prohibition be, and hereby is, dismissed. Relator’s claim in mandamus remains pending and will proceed pursuant to S.Ct.Prac.R. X.

Douglas, J., not participating.
